Libraries: 
	- pip install uv						  	-> Tool to manage multiple virtual environments with difference depences. 
	- pip instal pyarrow					  	-> Let export data in parquet format. 

File Types:
	- Dockerfile 							  	-> File type that describe exactly how we build a docker container; It has all the instructions to create a docker image and from this create a docker container.

Docker CLI: 

	- docker -V                        			-> Docker version
	- docker run hello-world		        	-> Check if docker is running correctly
	- docker run ubuntu			            	-> Create an ubuntu image/container
	- docker run -it ubuntu			        	-> Create and access an ubuntu image/container
	- docker run -it python:3.13.11-slim		-> Create and access a python image/container 
	- docker ps -a				              	-> See all the images and containers created and running
	- docker ps -aq				             	-> Get the Container's ID
	- docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq)		  		-> Force remove all the docker containers/images
	- docker run -it --entrypoint=bash python 3.13.11-slim -> Entry in a docker image/container.
	- docker run -it --entrypoint=bash -v ${pwd}\test:\app\test python:3.13.11-slim -> Load and save data into a container
	- docker build -t test:pandas .         	-> Create an image/container with a tag name within docker
	- docker build --no-cache -t test:pandas .  -> Create an image/container with a tag name within docker without using the cache
	- docker run -it --entrypoint=bash test:pandas -> Entry in a docker image/container.
	- docker run -it --entrypoint=bash --rm test:pandas -> Entry in a docker image/container an also remove all the info. after close it.
	- docker run -it --rm test:pandas 12				-> Execute a python script within an image with a predefined entry point not using the default bash.
	- rm -rf /								  	-> Removes all the files in the current container. 
	- 
	
PowerShell CLI: 

	- mkdir test                        -> Create a folder 
	- cd test                           -> Get the directory of the specified folder
	- cd ..								-> Get the previous directory
	- ni file1.txt; 
    echo 'Hello from host' > file1.txt -> ni creates a New Item and echo load info. to that specified item. 
	- cat file1.txt						-> display the content in the file. 
	- pwd                               -> Print working directory
	- ls 								-> Show all items in current directory
	- uv run python -V
	- uv init --python 3.13				-> Install an app within a virtual environment. 
	- uv add pandas pyarrow 			-> Install frameworks/libraries within a virtual environment
	
